Academic Honors

2024 Outdoor: Named USTFCCCA NCAA Division I Women's Outdoor Track Athlete of the Year... Named the Honda Sport Award Winner for Track & Field... Earned First Team All-American honors in both the 5000m and 10,000m... Secured her fifth and sixth career NCAA Individual Championships with wins in both the 5000m (14:52.18 - Collegiate Record) and 10,000m (31:46.09) at the NCAA Outdoor Championships... Qualified for the NCAA Outdoor Track & Field Championships in both the 5000m (15:19.76) and 10,000m (32:43.91) at the NCAA East Preliminaries (May 23/25)... Earned a gold medal for the second consecutive year at the SEC Outdoor Championships (May 11) in the 5000m with a outdoor school record time of 15:07.86... Set the NCAA and school record in the 10,000m with a time of 30:50.43, snapping a record that had stood for 14 years by 28 seconds, at the Bryan Clay Invitational (Apr. 11/12/13).

2024 Indoor: Titled the 2024 USTFCCCA NCAA Div. 1 National Women's Runner of the Year... Voted the 2024 USTFCCCA NCAA Div. I South Region Women's Runner of the Year... Named a 2024 USTFCCCA First Team All-American... Crowned the NCAA Individual Champion and reset her own collegiate record in the 5000m with a time of 14:52.79 and earned NCAA Individual Championship in 3000m with the third fastest time in collegiate history (8:41.50) in the 3000m at the NCAA Indoor Championships (Mar. 8/9)... Qualified for NCAA Indoor Championships (3000m & 5000m)... Secured two gold medals at the SEC Indoor Championships (Feb. 23/24) after placing first in the 3000m with a time of 8:42.29 (School Record, Meet Record, Facility Record) and anchoring the Women's DMR that set the meet record with a time of 10:53.29... Finished 1st in the Women's 5000m at the Sharon Colyear-Danville Season Opener (Dec. 2, 2023) and recorded a collegiate record, personal best, and school record time of 14:56.11 which granted her USTFCCCA Women's Athlete of the Week honors.

2023 Outdoor: Made her outdoor debut at the East Coast Relays, finishing first in the 5000m (15:32.44)... Won gold at the SEC Championships in the 5000m (15:33.43)... Finished third in the 5000m (15:33.43) at the NCAA East Preliminaries. Qualified for the National Championship in the 5000m... Won gold in the 5000m (15:30.57) at the NCAA Outdoor Championships. Named USTFCCCA Outdoor FirstTeam All-American in the 5000m.

2023 Indoor: Made her season debut at the Razorback Invitational, taking part in the school record distance medley relay team (10:57.58)… Competed in the 3000m at the David Hemery Valentine Invitational, running a time of 8:49.71, which further extends her school record in the event... Won gold in the 5000m (15:25.03) at the SEC Outdoor Championships.

2022 Outdoor: Paced the 5000 meters at the North Florida Invitational but did not finish ... smashed school record in 5000 meters (15:32.41) in silver-medal winning fashion at SEC Outdoor Championships ... member of Florida's 2022 SEC Outdoor Championship team ... broke school record again in 5000 meters (15:29.07) at NCAA East Prelims ... NCAA Qualifier in 5000 meters ... Second Team All-SEC and All-SEC Freshman Team (5000 meters) ... National Runner Up in the 5000 meters ... First Team All-American (5000m) ... member of Florida's NCAA Outdoor National Championship team

2022 Indoor: Made Florida Indoor debut at Rod McCravy Memorial Meet ... shattered the school record in the 3000 meters with a run of 8:53.89 ... ran the anchor leg on Florida's 4th-best DMR team in program history (11:00.92) ... named the SEC Women's Freshman of the Week for her performances at the Rod McCravy Memorial Meet (Feb. 1) ... recorded an NCAA-qualifying mark in the 3000 meters but was forced to scratch through injury

2021 Outdoor: Made her Outdoor collegiate debut at Tom Jones, finishing 8th in the 5,000m with a time of 17:14.57... named to the 2021 SEC First-Year Academic Honor Roll.

High School:

Attended East Lake High School

Florida state record holder in the 3,200 meters (10:10.45)

2019 FHSAA Class 3A Outdoor Finals gold medalist (3,200m)

2019 FHSAA Class 3A Outdoor Finals silver medalist (1,600m)

2019 FHSAA Class 3A Cross Country State Championships silver medalist

2018 FHSAA Class 3A Cross Country State Championships bronze medalist

MAJOR:

Graduated cum laude with bachelor's degree in Sports Management in May 2024.
